[normal]Royal Mail Privatisation and the threat to postal services[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]“
[normal]For the longer term, the universal service is just impractical
[normal]…
[normal]I would suggest in 3-5 years there will be only three maximum deliveries per week and that will be more than e
[normal]nough because most of what’s delivered now more and more is what’s called junk mail
[normal].”
[normal]As someone who knows more about postal economics than most, Mr Senior was even more 
[normal]downbeat about 
[normal]the long term future
[normal] of the USO
[normal]:
[normal]“Within 
[normal]15 years there will be no Roya
[normal]l Mail or no traditional letters service at all.”
[normal]Along with postal academics, many businesses leaders in the carrier sector are equally convinced that the universal postal service will change fundamentally. 
[normal]James Greenbury, Chief Executive of carrier 
[normal]Parcel2Go said recently that the six day delivery will be outdated and redundant in ten years time.
[normal] Mr Greenbury also suggests the privatisation will herald an era of price rises as well.
